Chinese manufacturer Xiaomi plans to enter the US smartphone market by next year, The Wall Street Journal reported. According to the report, Xiaomi could bring its smartphones to the US as early as the end of 2018. “We’ve always been considering entering the US market. We plan to start entering the market by end 2018, or by early 2019,” said Xiaomi. Xiaomi started selling its smartphones in Europe last year, and has seen success in many regions – including South Africa. The company’s success in the US will reportedly depend on partnerships with popular carriers.